      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, I just checked the kernel logs again. There's some weird pattern in the latency—it's not a standard buffer overflow. It's almost like the interrupts are being triggered by something external to the primary code. Before I hit the reset, can you explain why the stuttering is happening in such an irregular, non-linear way? It doesn't look like a hardware failure.",
