      "content": "The irregular latency you're observing could be attributed to a few potential factors outside of a buffer overflow. One possibility is that there are competing processes or background tasks that access shared resources unusually, creating deadlock situations or timing issues leading to stuttering. It might also be an issue with the real-time operating system settings or kernel parameter misconfigurations that lead to inefficient interrupt handling. Lastly, external electromagnetic interference could be causing sporadic responses. To pinpoint the issue, we could compare the system performance under varying load conditions or further investigate the environmental factors and system configurations impacting the interrupt patterns. A reset may offer a temporary reprieve but could be symptomatic of a deeper underlying problem that will persist until the root cause is fully understood and addressed.",
      "source": "target",
